    "updated_at": "2024-08-11T22:09:59Z",
    "body": "Turns out the issue was with my `format` setting for `[kubernetes]`. I was able to resolve by doing:\r\n\r\n```toml\r\n[kubernetes]\r\nformat = '[☸](blue) [$context]($style) \\($namespace\\) '\r\ndisabled = false\r\n\r\n# Shorten EKS clusters to only the important part of their name\r\n[[kubernetes.contexts]]\r\ncontext_pattern = 'arn.*\\/(?P<cluster>[\\w\\/]+)'\r\ncontext_alias = \"$cluster\"\r\nstyle = 'green'\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe noteworthy change being instead of using `$cluster` in my `format` I'm now using `$context` which will use the value of my `context_alias` variable being set by the individual contexts.",
